<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 4:23PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Iron
County through 445 PM MDT...
At 422 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 21
miles northeast of Beaver Dam, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Modena.
This includes Utah Route 56 between mile markers 10 and 23.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
